File: Former Home Affairs Minister Malusi Gigaba. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - State Capture Inquiry Chairperson Deputy Chief Justice, Raymond Zondo has granted Malusi Gigaba leave to cross-examine his estranged wife, Norma Mngoma before the end of this month. Mngoma completed her testimony on Friday, while the former minister took the stand before lunchtime. READ: Gigaba told me about Gupta visits: Norma Mngoma In her testimony on Friday Mngoma said she was shocked that her affidavit was leaked ahead of her appearance at the inquiry.